<examples>
The following examples illustrate the expected level of rigour and the tone of a well-formed estimation. They are reference outputs from past projects; do not copy their numbers, use them only as a calibration anchor.

<example>
<project_description>
A small Angular web project for labeling defects in images of wind turbine blades
</project_description>
<estimation>
| phase            | duration_weeks | cost_eur | confidence_pct |
|------------------|----------------|----------|----------------|
| Discovery        | 1              | 300      | 75             |
| Design           | 1              | 1,000    | 80             |
| Implementation   | 4              | 1,000    | 80             |
| QA               | 1              | 1,000    | 75             |
| Launch           | 1              | 1,500    | 80             |

Totals: 1344 total_hours, 4,800 total_cost_eur, 8 total_duration_weeks.
Team: 1 product designer (part-time), 1 backend developer, 1 frontend developer.
</estimation>
</example>

